19static constexpr Register kScratchRegisters[] = {r8, ip, r1};
20static constexpr int kNumScratchRegisters = arraysize(kScratchRegisters);

22#ifdef DEBUG
23inline bool Clobbers(Register target, MemOperand op) {
24 return op.rb() == target || op.rx() == target;

29class BaselineAssembler::ScratchRegisterScope {
30 public:
31 explicit ScratchRegisterScope(BaselineAssembler* assembler)
32 : assembler_(assembler),
33 prev_scope_(assembler->scratch_register_scope_),
34 registers_used_(prev_scope_ == nullptr ? 0
35 : prev_scope_->registers_used_) {
36 assembler_->scratch_register_scope_ = this;
37 }
38 ~ScratchRegisterScope() { assembler_->scratch_register_scope_ = prev_scope_; }
39
40 Register AcquireScratch() {
41 DCHECK_LT(registers_used_, detail::kNumScratchRegisters);
42 return detail::kScratchRegisters[registers_used_++];
43 }
44
45 private:
46 BaselineAssembler* assembler_;
47 ScratchRegisterScope* prev_scope_;
48 int registers_used_;
49};

51#define __ assm->
52// s390x helper
53template <int width = 64>
54static void JumpIfHelper(MacroAssembler* assm, Condition cc, Register lhs,
55 Register rhs, Label* target) {
56 static_assert(width == 64 || width == 32,
57 "only support 64 and 32 bit compare");
58 if (width == 64) {
59 if (is_signed(cc)) {
60 __ CmpS64(lhs, rhs);
61 } else {
62 __ CmpU64(lhs, rhs);
63 }
64 } else {
65 if (is_signed(cc)) {
66 __ CmpS32(lhs, rhs);
67 } else {
68 __ CmpU32(lhs, rhs);
69 }
70 }
71 __ b(to_condition(cc), target);
72}
73
74#undef __
75
76#define __ masm_->

143void BaselineAssembler::JumpIf(Condition cc, Register lhs, const Operand& rhs,
144 Label* target, Label::Distance) {
145 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm_);
146 if (is_signed(cc)) {
147 __ CmpS64(lhs, rhs);

154void BaselineAssembler::JumpIfObjectTypeFast(Condition cc, Register object,
155 InstanceType instance_type,
156 Label* target,
157 Label::Distance distance) {
158 ScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
159 Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
160 JumpIfObjectType(cc, object, instance_type, scratch, target, distance);
161}

163void BaselineAssembler::JumpIfObjectType(Condition cc, Register object,
164 InstanceType instance_type,
165 Register map, Label* target,
166 Label::Distance) {
167 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm_);
168 ScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
169 Register type = temps.AcquireScratch();
170 __ LoadMap(map, object);
171 __ LoadU16(type, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
172 JumpIf(cc, type, Operand(instance_type), target);
173}
174
175void BaselineAssembler::JumpIfInstanceType(Condition cc, Register map,
176 InstanceType instance_type,
177 Label* target, Label::Distance) {
178 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm_);
179 ScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
180 Register type = temps.AcquireScratch();
181 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
182 __ AssertNotSmi(map);
183 __ CompareObjectType(map, type, type, MAP_TYPE);
184 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue);
185 }
186 __ LoadU16(type, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
187 JumpIf(cc, type, Operand(instance_type), target);
188}

222void BaselineAssembler::JumpIfTagged(Condition cc, Register value,
223 MemOperand operand, Label* target,
224 Label::Distance) {
225 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm_);
226 DCHECK(operand.rb() == fp || operand.rx() == fp);
227 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
228 MemOperand addr =
229 MemOperand(operand.rx(), operand.rb(), operand.offset() + stack_bias);
230 __ LoadTaggedField(ip, addr, r0);
231 } else {
232 __ LoadTaggedField(ip, operand, r0);
233 }
234 JumpIfHelper<COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? 32 : 64>(masm_, cc, value, ip, target);
235}

298template <typename Arg>
299inline Register ToRegister(BaselineAssembler* basm,
300 BaselineAssembler::ScratchRegisterScope* scope,
301 Arg arg) {
302 Register reg = scope->AcquireScratch();
303 basm->Move(reg, arg);
304 return reg;
305}
306inline Register ToRegister(BaselineAssembler* basm,
307 BaselineAssembler::ScratchRegisterScope* scope,
308 Register reg) {
309 return reg;
310}

312template <typename... Args>
313struct PushAllHelper;
314template <>
315struct PushAllHelper<> {
316 static int Push(BaselineAssembler* basm) { return 0; }
317 static int PushReverse(BaselineAssembler* basm) { return 0; }
318};
319// TODO(ishell): try to pack sequence of pushes into one instruction by
320// looking at regiser codes. For example, Push(r1, r2, r5, r0, r3, r4)
321// could be generated as two pushes: Push(r1, r2, r5) and Push(r0, r3, r4).
322template <typename Arg>
323struct PushAllHelper<Arg> {
324 static int Push(BaselineAssembler* basm, Arg arg) {
325 BaselineAssembler::ScratchRegisterScope scope(basm);
326 basm->masm()->Push(ToRegister(basm, &scope, arg));
327 return 1;
328 }
329 static int PushReverse(BaselineAssembler* basm, Arg arg) {
330 return Push(basm, arg);
331 }
332};
333// TODO(ishell): try to pack sequence of pushes into one instruction by
334// looking at regiser codes. For example, Push(r1, r2, r5, r0, r3, r4)
335// could be generated as two pushes: Push(r1, r2, r5) and Push(r0, r3, r4).
336template <typename Arg, typename... Args>
337struct PushAllHelper<Arg, Args...> {
338 static int Push(BaselineAssembler* basm, Arg arg, Args... args) {
339 PushAllHelper<Arg>::Push(basm, arg);
340 return 1 + PushAllHelper<Args...>::Push(basm, args...);
341 }
342 static int PushReverse(BaselineAssembler* basm, Arg arg, Args... args) {
343 int nargs = PushAllHelper<Args...>::PushReverse(basm, args...);
344 PushAllHelper<Arg>::Push(basm, arg);
345 return nargs + 1;
346 }
347};
348template <>
349struct PushAllHelper<interpreter::RegisterList> {
350 static int Push(BaselineAssembler* basm, interpreter::RegisterList list) {
351 for (int reg_index = 0; reg_index < list.register_count(); ++reg_index) {
352 PushAllHelper<interpreter::Register>::Push(basm, list[reg_index]);
353 }
354 return list.register_count();
355 }
356 static int PushReverse(BaselineAssembler* basm,
357 interpreter::RegisterList list) {
358 for (int reg_index = list.register_count() - 1; reg_index >= 0;
359 --reg_index) {
360 PushAllHelper<interpreter::Register>::Push(basm, list[reg_index]);
361 }
362 return list.register_count();
363 }
364};
365
366template <typename... T>
367struct PopAllHelper;
368template <>
369struct PopAllHelper<> {
370 static void Pop(BaselineAssembler* basm) {}
371};
372// TODO(ishell): try to pack sequence of pops into one instruction by
373// looking at regiser codes. For example, Pop(r1, r2, r5, r0, r3, r4)
374// could be generated as two pops: Pop(r1, r2, r5) and Pop(r0, r3, r4).
375template <>
376struct PopAllHelper<Register> {
377 static void Pop(BaselineAssembler* basm, Register reg) {
378 basm->masm()->Pop(reg);
379 }
380};
381template <typename... T>
382struct PopAllHelper<Register, T...> {
383 static void Pop(BaselineAssembler* basm, Register reg, T... tail) {
384 PopAllHelper<Register>::Pop(basm, reg);
385 PopAllHelper<T...>::Pop(basm, tail...);
386 }
387};
388
389} // namespace detail

463void BaselineAssembler::TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(Register scratch_and_result,
464 Register feedback_vector,
465 FeedbackSlot slot,
466 Label* on_result,
467 Label::Distance) {
468 Label fallthrough;
469 LoadTaggedField(scratch_and_result, feedback_vector,
470 FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt()));
471 __ LoadWeakValue(scratch_and_result, scratch_and_result, &fallthrough);
472
473 // Is it marked_for_deoptimization? If yes, clear the slot.
474 {
475 ScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
476
477 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
478 __ LoadTaggedField(
479 scratch_and_result,
480 FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
481
482 Register scratch = temps.AcquireScratch();
483 __ TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch_and_result, scratch);
484 __ beq(on_result);
485 __ mov(scratch, __ ClearedValue());
486 StoreTaggedFieldNoWriteBarrier(
487 feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt()),
488 scratch);
489 }
490
491 __ bind(&fallthrough);
492 Move(scratch_and_result, 0);
493}

495void BaselineAssembler::AddToInterruptBudgetAndJumpIfNotExceeded(
496 int32_t weight, Label* skip_interrupt_label) {
497 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm_);
498 ScratchRegisterScope scratch_scope(this);
499 Register feedback_cell = scratch_scope.AcquireScratch();
500 LoadFeedbackCell(feedback_cell);
501
502 Register interrupt_budget = scratch_scope.AcquireScratch();
503 __ LoadU32(
504 interrupt_budget,
505 FieldMemOperand(feedback_cell, FeedbackCell::kInterruptBudgetOffset));
506 // Remember to set flags as part of the add!
507 __ AddS32(interrupt_budget, Operand(weight));
508 __ StoreU32(
509 interrupt_budget,
510 FieldMemOperand(feedback_cell, FeedbackCell::kInterruptBudgetOffset), r0);
511 if (skip_interrupt_label) {
512 // Use compare flags set by add
513 DCHECK_LT(weight, 0);
514 __ b(ge, skip_interrupt_label);
515 }
516}
517
518void BaselineAssembler::AddToInterruptBudgetAndJumpIfNotExceeded(
519 Register weight, Label* skip_interrupt_label) {
520 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm_);
521 ScratchRegisterScope scratch_scope(this);
522 Register feedback_cell = scratch_scope.AcquireScratch();
523 LoadFeedbackCell(feedback_cell);
524
525 Register interrupt_budget = scratch_scope.AcquireScratch();
526 __ LoadU32(
527 interrupt_budget,
528 FieldMemOperand(feedback_cell, FeedbackCell::kInterruptBudgetOffset));
529 // Remember to set flags as part of the add!
530 __ AddS32(interrupt_budget, interrupt_budget, weight);
531 __ StoreU32(
532 interrupt_budget,
533 FieldMemOperand(feedback_cell, FeedbackCell::kInterruptBudgetOffset));
534 if (skip_interrupt_label) __ b(ge, skip_interrupt_label);
535}

537void BaselineAssembler::LdaContextSlot(Register context, uint32_t index,
538 uint32_t depth) {
539 for (; depth > 0; --depth) {
540 LoadTaggedField(context, context, Context::kPreviousOffset);
541 }
542 LoadTaggedField(kInterpreterAccumulatorRegister, context,
543 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index));
544}
545
546void BaselineAssembler::StaContextSlot(Register context, Register value,
547 uint32_t index, uint32_t depth) {
548 for (; depth > 0; --depth) {
549 LoadTaggedField(context, context, Context::kPreviousOffset);
550 }
551 StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(context, Context::OffsetOfElementAt(index),
552 value);
553}
554
555void BaselineAssembler::LdaModuleVariable(Register context, int cell_index,
556 uint32_t depth) {
557 for (; depth > 0; --depth) {
558 LoadTaggedField(context, context, Context::kPreviousOffset);
559 }
560 LoadTaggedField(context, context, Context::kExtensionOffset);
561 if (cell_index > 0) {
562 LoadTaggedField(context, context, SourceTextModule::kRegularExportsOffset);
563 // The actual array index is (cell_index - 1).
564 cell_index -= 1;
565 } else {
566 LoadTaggedField(context, context, SourceTextModule::kRegularImportsOffset);
567 // The actual array index is (-cell_index - 1).
568 cell_index = -cell_index - 1;
569 }
570 LoadFixedArrayElement(context, context, cell_index);
571 LoadTaggedField(kInterpreterAccumulatorRegister, context, Cell::kValueOffset);
572}
573
574void BaselineAssembler::StaModuleVariable(Register context, Register value,
575 int cell_index, uint32_t depth) {
576 for (; depth > 0; --depth) {
577 LoadTaggedField(context, context, Context::kPreviousOffset);
578 }
579 LoadTaggedField(context, context, Context::kExtensionOffset);
580 LoadTaggedField(context, context, SourceTextModule::kRegularExportsOffset);
581
582 // The actual array index is (cell_index - 1).
583 cell_index -= 1;
584 LoadFixedArrayElement(context, context, cell_index);
585 StoreTaggedFieldWithWriteBarrier(context, Cell::kValueOffset, value);
586}

588void BaselineAssembler::IncrementSmi(MemOperand lhs) {
589 Register scratch = ip;
590 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
591 DCHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
592 DCHECK(lhs.rb() == fp || lhs.rx() == fp);
593 MemOperand addr = MemOperand(lhs.rx(), lhs.rb(), lhs.offset() + stack_bias);
594 __ LoadS32(scratch, addr);
595 __ AddU32(scratch, Operand(Smi::FromInt(1)));
596 __ StoreU32(scratch, addr);
597 } else {
598 __ SmiUntag(scratch, lhs);
599 __ AddU64(scratch, Operand(1));
600 __ SmiTag(scratch);
601 __ StoreU64(scratch, lhs);
602 }
603}

605void BaselineAssembler::Word32And(Register output, Register lhs, int rhs) {
606 __ AndP(output, lhs, Operand(rhs));
607}

609void BaselineAssembler::Switch(Register reg, int case_value_base,
610 Label** labels, int num_labels) {
611 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm_);
612 Label fallthrough, jump_table;
613 if (case_value_base != 0) {
614 __ AddS64(reg, Operand(-case_value_base));
615 }
616
617 // Mostly copied from code-generator-arm.cc
618 ScratchRegisterScope scope(this);
619 JumpIf(kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, reg, Operand(num_labels), &fallthrough);
620 // Ensure to emit the constant pool first if necessary.
621 int entry_size_log2 = 3;
622 __ ShiftLeftU32(reg, reg, Operand(entry_size_log2));
623 __ larl(r1, &jump_table);
624 __ lay(reg, MemOperand(reg, r1));
625 __ b(reg);
626 __ b(&fallthrough);
627 __ bind(&jump_table);
628 for (int i = 0; i < num_labels; ++i) {
629 __ b(labels[i], Label::kFar);
630 __ nop();
631 }
632 __ bind(&fallthrough);
633}

639void BaselineAssembler::EmitReturn(MacroAssembler* masm) {
640 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
641 BaselineAssembler basm(masm);
642
643 Register weight = BaselineLeaveFrameDescriptor::WeightRegister();
644 Register params_size = BaselineLeaveFrameDescriptor::ParamsSizeRegister();
645
646 {
647 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Update Interrupt Budget");
648
649 Label skip_interrupt_label;
650 __ AddToInterruptBudgetAndJumpIfNotExceeded(weight, &skip_interrupt_label);
651 {
652 __ masm()->SmiTag(params_size);
653 __ Push(params_size, kInterpreterAccumulatorRegister);
654
655 __ LoadContext(kContextRegister);
656 __ LoadFunction(kJSFunctionRegister);
657 __ Push(kJSFunctionRegister);
658 __ CallRuntime(Runtime::kBytecodeBudgetInterrupt_Sparkplug, 1);
659
660 __ Pop(kInterpreterAccumulatorRegister, params_size);
661 __ masm()->SmiUntag(params_size);
662 }
663
664 __ Bind(&skip_interrupt_label);
665 }
666
667 BaselineAssembler::ScratchRegisterScope temps(&basm);
668 Register actual_params_size = temps.AcquireScratch();
669 // Compute the size of the actual parameters + receiver (in bytes).
670 __ Move(actual_params_size,
671 MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
672
673 // If actual is bigger than formal, then we should use it to free up the stack
674 // arguments.
675 Label corrected_args_count;
676 JumpIfHelper(__ masm(), kGreaterThanEqual, params_size, actual_params_size,
677 &corrected_args_count);
678 __ masm()->mov(params_size, actual_params_size);
679 __ Bind(&corrected_args_count);
680
681 // Leave the frame (also dropping the register file).
682 __ masm()->LeaveFrame(StackFrame::BASELINE);
683
684 // Drop receiver + arguments.
685 __ masm()->DropArguments(params_size, MacroAssembler::kCountIsInteger,
686 MacroAssembler::kCountIncludesReceiver);
687 __ masm()->Ret();
688}
689
690#undef __
691
692inline void EnsureAccumulatorPreservedScope::AssertEqualToAccumulator(
693 Register reg) {
694 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
695 assembler_->masm()->CmpU32(reg, kInterpreterAccumulatorRegister);
696 } else {
697 assembler_->masm()->CmpU64(reg, kInterpreterAccumulatorRegister);
698 }
699 assembler_->masm()->Assert(eq, AbortReason::kAccumulatorClobbered);
700}
